curlftpfs: CurlFtpFS is a filesystem for accessing FTP hosts based on FUSE and libcurl
curlftpfs:
curlftpfs: CurlFtpFS differentiates itself from other FTP filesystems because it features:
curlftpfs: - SSLv3 and TLSv1 support
curlftpfs: - connecting through tunneling HTTP proxies
curlftpfs: - automatically reconnection if the server times out
curlftpfs: - transform absolute symlinks to point back into the ftp file system
